{"TopicId":140511,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Why does my station rotate?","CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-25T20:11:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-25T20:11:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo while in orbit around kerbin, I have this station I\u0027m working on. It\u0027s really long, so this might be the cause of the problem, also the center of mass isn\u0027t directly in the center of the station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what is happening is the station rotates in orbit, even after I use time warp to stop it. I don\u0027t have it moving, so I don\u0027t know why this is happening. What can I do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-26T15:16:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it rotate once per orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Padishar","CreatedById":97386,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-26T15:44:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have a trim applied? \u00A0That could be causing your station to slowly spin up again after timewarp. \u00A0Try hitting Alt-X to reset the trim and see if it stops...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SnakyLeVrai","CreatedById":135852,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-26T16:21:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this too with large space stations that have many pieces. I\u0027ve limited this effect by using cargo bays to stuff much of the parts inside. The structural parts are now Mk3 size and include cargo bays, it means less parts to wobble together and enter resonance...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe whole station has less parts (due to better skills after hundreds of KSP hours) and is less prone to auto-rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember this but: aren\u0027t cargo bays including \u0022invisible struts\u0022 now in 1.1.2? (like airstreams)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/VfGqA/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T14:59:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222602216\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464275791\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/26/2016 at 11:16 AM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it rotate once per orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know what you mean by this, but I\u0027ll try to give a good answer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt rotates very slowly. like, it turns around a full 90 degrees about every 50 orbits. It shouldn\u0027t do this, though. It should stay still.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222602269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464277474\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297386\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Padishar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/26/2016 at 11:44 AM, Padishar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have a trim applied? \u00A0That could be causing your station to slowly spin up again after timewarp. \u00A0Try hitting Alt-X to reset the trim and see if it stops...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried this, didn\u0027t seem to work. I\u0027m on mac so what would the key configuration be?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:12:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, with that description, I can say that yes I am seeing it too -- even with small ships. There are\u00A0small phantom forces that make\u00A0everything start to rotate slowly and drift off their initial orientation if you just sit and watch them. It doesn\u0027t happen on rails. I think it happens because all the parts of any ship are pushing on each other, and the forces do not all cancel perfectly to zero\u00A0(the way they should)\u00A0because of rounding and \u0022precision\u0022\u00A0errors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Padishar","CreatedById":97386,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:12:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606590\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464533991\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144023\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nickrulercreator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, nickrulercreator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried this, didn\u0027t seem to work. I\u0027m on mac so what would the key configuration be?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a mac I guess it would be option-x\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:13:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606606\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464534766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297386\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Padishar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Padishar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a mac I guess it would be option-x\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntried that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nstill didn\u0027t work.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nXD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:16:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have SAS on?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:20:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606614\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464535015\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lo Var Lachland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Lo Var Lachland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have SAS on?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlways do\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:22:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464535207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144023\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nickrulercreator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, nickrulercreator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlways do\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder... Just a few quick questions. Do you have RCS along the station?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nickrulercreator","CreatedById":144023,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T15:56:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606623\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464535379\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lo Var Lachland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, Lo Var Lachland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder... Just a few quick questions. Do you have RCS along the station?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot usually, only if I\u0027m moving the station back to the position I want it in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T00:35:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222606661\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464537396\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144023\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nickrulercreator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, nickrulercreator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot usually, only if I\u0027m moving the station back to the position I want it in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWeird. I\u0027ll have to investigate further.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}